Post title: Editing quiz questions from a preview is confusing
Post description: Hi, I have discovered -- as have several colleagues -- that choosing the "Edit" link from a quiz preview doe snot work as expected. In particular, if you make changes to the question and then return to the preview, the changes do not show up. I haven't worked out whether the changes stick at all (e.g., if you exit the preview and start a new one) or if they're discarded, but regardless, this is quite annoying. Version is Moodle 4 (sorry, I don't know how to find the specific sub-version but I'm sure someone else from Glasgow will be able to give the full details)
Comments associated with the post: 
Comment 1: Yes, I am afraid that this is a known issue with the new system ( MDL-78547 ). It is really annoying for users and needs to be fixed, but unfortunately no-one has had time to get to it yet. The changes to the question are saved just fine, and if you clieck "Start a new preview" then the changes show up. (But users should not have to resort to that work-around.) This issue is somewhere on the todo list of my team at the Open University, but at the moment there quite a lot of other (more urgent for us) things above it, so if anyone else gets there first, we would not mind.
Comment 2: Just to say MDL-78547 was integrated last week, so that fix will be included in the next point releases (4.2.7, 4.3.4 and 4.4 in mid April).
Comment 3: I thought I could share a small script to work around this issue while waiting for it to be resolved. You can place it in 'Course administration / Appearance / Additional HTML' if you have access, or else you can place it in a block that displays on all pages. 
```text
<script src="https://
ajax
.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.6.1/jquery.min.js"></script>
<script>
$(document).ready(function() {
// AUTOMATIC "START A NEW ATTEMPT"
//________________________________________________________________________

    // WHILE ON THE QUESTION EDIT PAGE
    if ( window.location.href.indexOf("question/bank/editquestion/question.php") > -1 && window.location.href.indexOf("attempt.php") > -1) {
        // ON CLICKING THE SAVE BUTTON, 
        // SET A SESSION STORAGE KEY (questionsaved) TO "YES".
        $("input#id_submitbutton").on("click", function(){
            sessionStorage.setItem("questionsaved", "yes");
        });
    }

    // WHILE ON THE PREVIEW PAGE
    if ( window.location.href.indexOf("mod/quiz/attempt.php") > -1 ) {
        // RETREIVE THE VALUE OF THE questionsaved SESSION STORAGE KEY.
        var dcquestionsaved = sessionStorage.getItem("questionsaved");
        // IF THE VALUE OF THE questionsaved SESSION STORAGE KEY IS EQUAL TO "YES",
        // TRIGGER THE "Start a new preview" BUTTON AND RESET THE VALUE OF questionsaved
        if( dcquestionsaved == "yes" ){
            $("#mod_quiz_navblock button[type=submit]").trigger("click");
            sessionStorage.setItem("questionsaved", "initialized");
        }
    }
//________________________________________________________________________
);
</script>
```
Comment 4: I should have mentioned that the script automatically clicks on the 'Start a new preview' button for you, so you don't have to do it yourself. It's done automatically, so you won't forget! (And of course, at the beginning of the code, one should read the comment "Start a new preview" and not "Start a new attempt".)
Comment 5: Automatically clicking 'Start new preview' is a good solution in simple cases, but it is not a complete solution. The case it does not handle is when the quiz uses random questions. Then, restarting the preview might end up showing a different question to the one you edited. So, while Dominique's fix is useful, we need something more complicated for the proper fix in Moodle core, which is why it is taking more time. (In case anyone was wondering.)
